args: I'm going to do whatever is necessary\nto be the best bride I can be!
Wearing that dress again, are you?
Of course. If I don't wear this dress,\nI'll just be regular old me.
What's wrong with regular old you?
When I wear this dress, it makes me feel\nas if I can aim higher and fly farther.\nIt's like I can do anything!
*sigh* But for what PURPOSE are you\ndoing all of this high aiming and flying\nand...so forth?
So I can be the perfect bride, of course!
When my sister-in-law, Mei, got engaged,\nshe focused on improving herself so she\nwould be the best bride possible.
Well, I suppose there is nothing wrong\nwith striving to better oneself.
Nope! There isn't. And that's why I'm\ngoing to learn to cook with MAGIC!
...And there we have it!\nWell, Cleo? Thoughts?
Hmm... Well, as a complete meal,\nI would have to say it's rather ordinary.
Er, that's the GOOD kind of ordinary, right?
The way you put it together was adroit,\nbut the actual menu itself lacks anything\nparticularly noteworthy.
It feels as if you simply threw food\ntogether without thinking about it.
But I was trying to make a home-cooked\nmeal full of nutritious love!
Was it the ingredients that were lacking?\nPerhaps the number of dishes?
I think what it lacks is passion—and the\nway to solve that is to have someone else\njoin you at the table.
A bride—or any chef—is best able to\ncreate delicious meals when they're\ndoing it for someone special.
Without that person, the meal becomes\nlittle more than sustenance.
So I was lacking someone special...
Ah, well. I'll have to worry about this later.\nRight now, I need to get ready for my\nfirst meet-and-greet with the groom!

...Actually, I wonder if that might help
my current problem. Even if he isn't my
actual lover, perhaps meeting him would
help to better my bridal ways.
In that case, I'm going to get ready!

You must be Emily. Ah, it's good to see
my judgment wasn't mistaken when it
came to picking out the dress—it looks
absolutely stunning on you!
(I may be a false bride, but I still have to\nimagine that I'm doing my best for the\nsake of the man I love.)
(Imagine, Xania! Imagine as you have\nnever imagined before!)
You were staring off into space.\nDoes your time with me bore you so?
(I'd hoped to feel much more effervescent\nupon our first meeting.)
...Well, I'm home. And so very tired!\nIt appears I've a long way to go on my\npath to becoming the perfect bride.
Well, well. If it isn't Xania.\nWhat's with the stylish getup?
Hello, Mym. Er, it's a rather long story,\nbut basically I've been entrusted with\nthe role of being a bride.
Ooo, that sounds simply DELIGHTFUL!\nBut then, why do you look so dour?
Where there are booms, there's Sinoa.\n*sigh* Let's go help the daft thing out\nbefore we get to hearing your woes.
Sinoa? Are you alive? That was quite\nthe explosion, even by your standards.
S-sorry! ...Oh, and I'm alive, if that\nwasn't obvious from the speaking.
Where did I go wrong? It should have\nbeen reproduced perfectly! Hmm...

What say we get this cleaned up first,
then try to suss out the possible cause.
Come now, it will go quickly if all three
of us pitch in.
...Whew! I think we're back to normal.\nOr as normal as I ever get, I suppose.
And it's mostly because of Xania's nifty\ncleaning magic—so perhaps you should\nstop woolgathering and THANK her.
Oh, it was nothing so impressive.
You're a true lifesaver, Xania. Thank you.\nStill, I refuse to give up! I will soldier on!
Someday, I WILL create a wormhole\nand travel to the past, no matter how\nmany explosions it takes!
What, the explosions? Well, you see,\nwhen one attempts to warp space-time,\nthe effects of both force and mass begin—
Er, no. I meant YOU. The fact you've\ndedicated yourself so completely to a\nsingle goal is truly laudable.
In the same way, I'm impressed by how\nMym is able to dedicate herself so\nwholly to her love of the prince.
Is THAT what you were worried about?\nThat you have nothing in your life which\ndemands a similar passion?
But you DO have something like that!\nDidn't your father leave you a scroll\nor magical beans or something?
It was a book: ＂Better Living Through\nSpellcraft.＂ And yes, it is incredibly\nimportant to me.
But that is different; it's something that\nwas GIVEN to me. The two of you have\npassions that came about organically.
I want to be the best bride I can be,\nbut unless I'm able to dedicate myself\nto it heart and soul, I don't think...
Why are you trying so hard to be a\nperfect bride in the first place, Xania?
Well, I suppose I find the idea\nto be rather...nice.
And THAT'S what you're beating yourself\nup about? An idea that's ＂nice＂?

Then you're never going to be able to
feel the spark of inspiration you seek!
Neither one of us chase our passions
because we find them to be ＂nice.＂
Indeed. I give my all to my work because\nit burns inside me like the fire of a molten\nmagma core!
So think about yourself for a moment.\nFind your REASON for trying so hard.
Nope. Nothing. All I can come up with\nis that it feels...nice.

So perhaps my problem isn't a lack of
general household knowledge—or a
loved one or partner to share it with.
Perhaps I simply lack the WILL.
You don't lack will, Xania.\nYou lack LOVE.
And since you're not in love, you can't\npossibly give something like this your all!\nThat's why you only see it as ＂nice.＂
So without both the proper will and love,\nI'll never be a perfect bride...
Well, I promise you this: I AM going to\nfind what I love someday!
